# Copy to `.env.local` for local dev (never commit real secrets).
# Production: set the same keys in Vercel → Project → Settings → Environment Variables.

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Ops alerts (optional) — fired on coach application updates and draft governance events.
# If both are unset, `notifyOpsEvent` in lib/ops-alerts.ts does nothing (no outbound HTTP).
#
# You must supply real URLs yourself (n8n Webhook node, or any HTTPS endpoint that
# forwards to Discord / OpenClaw / etc.). Do not commit live URLs with secrets in paths.
#
# N8N_WEBHOOK_URL=
# Example: https://aab-n8n.moodmnky.com/webhook/<webhook-id>
# In n8n: workflow must be ACTIVE; Webhook node HTTP method must be POST (app sends JSON).
#
# OPENCLAW_ALERT_WEBHOOK_URL=
# Optional second sink: e.g. small bridge that posts to a staff channel or OpenClaw.
# Not the OpenClaw MCP gateway URL — a plain POST webhook you control.
#
# Payload (JSON POST): { event, source: "poke-mnky", ts, ... }
# Events: coach_application_status, draft_session_pending_admin_approval,
#         draft_session_governance_approved
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

N8N_WEBHOOK_URL=
OPENCLAW_ALERT_WEBHOOK_URL=

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Cursor: poke-mnky-n8n MCP (workflow list/get/edit — NOT the webhook above)
# Create a key in n8n: Settings → API → Create API Key.
# Point `.cursor/mcp.json` at these via "env": { "N8N_API_KEY": "${env:N8N_API_KEY}", ... }
# Restart Cursor after changing MCP env.
#
# N8N_API_URL=https://aab-n8n.moodmnky.com
# N8N_API_KEY=n8n_api_...
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
